She posted the photo of the certificate on X, saying: “Two weeks ago a member of the public sent a passport application to @ukhomeoffice for their six month old baby girl. “day, the birth certificate was returned torn with the word “Israel” written on it. Parents are understandably very concerned about this incident. We are asking the Home Office to investigate how this happened. The Ministry of the Interior has responsibility for law enforcement and the security of the Jewish community.”
Speaking in the House of Commons today, Policing Minister Chris Phillips stressed that “whenever and wherever crime involving anti-Semitism occurs, this Government expects the police to fully investigate the incident and work with the Crown Prosecution Service to bring the perpetrators to justice in justice”.
